UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1600
1 A JOINT RESOLUTION designating the Elmer Carmon Milliner and PFC
2 Clarence Ozbert Milliner Memorial Bridges in Grayson County.
3 WHEREAS, Elmer Carmon Milliner was a retired farmer and a retired associate
4 with General Electric, having been with the company for 34 years; and
5 WHEREAS, Elmer Milliner was a Korean War Veteran who received the Purple
6 Heart, two Bronze Stars, a Silver Star, a Combat Infantryman Medal, a Korean War
7 Medal, the Army Good Conduct Medal, a United Nations Service Medal, and a National
8 Defense Service Medal; and
9 WHEREAS, Elmer Milliner was a loyal and faithful member of the St. Paul
10 Catholic Church and a member of the Honorable Order of the Kentucky Colonels; and
11 WHEREAS, Private First Class Clarence Ozbert Milliner served in the United
12 States Marine Corps during World War II. He was killed in action on February 24, 1945,
13 in the Pacific Theater, and was buried at sea; and
14 WHEREAS, PFC Clarence Milliner received the World War II Victory Medal, the
15 Purple Heart, a Combat Action Service Ribbon, the American Campaign Medal, a
16 Marine Corps Presidential Unit Citation Medal, a Good Conduct Campaign Medal, the
17 Asiatic-Pacific Campaign Medal, and the Marine Corps Expeditionary Medal; and
18 WHEREAS, Grayson County considers Elmer Carmon Milliner and Clarence
19 Ozbert Milliner to be honorable sons of the Commonwealth, and there is strong local
20 support to ensure they are recognized for their service and bravery;
21 NOW, THEREFORE,
22 Be it resolved by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
23 Section 1. The Transportation Cabinet shall designate the bridge on Kentucky
24 Route 920 in Grayson County over Clifty Creek (Bridge ID #043B00084N) as the "Elmer
25 Carmon Milliner Memorial Bridge" and shall, within 30 days of the effective date of this
26 Resolution, erect appropriate signage denoting this designation.
27 Section 2. The Transportation Cabinet shall designate the bridge on Kentucky
